      • getCheckMessages

        public java.lang.String[] getCheckMessages​()
        Description copied from class: Check
        Each check has a set amount of error messages, used to highlight issues and pass information between eachother.

        This method is used primarily for testing and scanning files within a check.

        e.g: in the check for A, it will be necessary to also check for B and act according to the B error message.

        This is done as such 

        
 	Check check = UXCheckFactory.getInstance(check.class);
 	List<Issue> checkIssues = tableCheck.scanFile(this.getContext());
        Specified by:
        getCheckMessages in class Check
        Returns:
        A String array of this check's error messages
